53/*
54 * Used to store addresses from ListenAddr directives. These may be
55 * incomplete, as they may specify addresses that need to be merged
56 * with any ports requested by ListenPort.
57 */
58struct queued_listenaddr {
59 char *addr;
60 int port; /* <=0 if unspecified */
61 char *rdomain;
62};
63
64/* Resolved listen addresses, grouped by optional routing domain */
65struct listenaddr {
66 char *rdomain;
67 struct addrinfo *addrs;
68};
69
70typedef struct {
71 u_int num_ports;
72 u_int ports_from_cmdline;
73 int ports[MAX_PORTS]; /* Port number to listen on. */
74 struct queued_listenaddr *queued_listen_addrs;
75 u_int num_queued_listens;
76 struct listenaddr *listen_addrs;
77 u_int num_listen_addrs;
78 int address_family; /* Address family used by the server. */
79
80 char *routing_domain; /* Bind session to routing domain */
81
82 char **host_key_files; /* Files containing host keys. */
83 int *host_key_file_userprovided; /* Key was specified by user. */
84 u_int num_host_key_files; /* Number of files for host keys. */
85 char **host_cert_files; /* Files containing host certs. */
86 u_int num_host_cert_files; /* Number of files for host certs. */
87
88 char *host_key_agent; /* ssh-agent socket for host keys. */
89 char *pid_file; /* Where to put our pid */
90 int login_grace_time; /* Disconnect if no auth in this time
91 * (sec). */
92 int permit_root_login; /* PERMIT_*, see above */
93 int ignore_rhosts; /* Ignore .rhosts and .shosts. */
94 int ignore_root_rhosts; /* Ignore .rhosts and .shosts for root;
95 defaults to ignore_rhosts if not
96 given. */
97 int ignore_user_known_hosts; /* Ignore ~/.ssh/known_hosts
98 * for RhostsRsaAuth */
99 int print_motd; /* If true, print /etc/motd. */
100 int print_lastlog; /* If true, print lastlog */
101 int x11_forwarding; /* If true, permit inet (spoofing) X11 fwd. */
102 int x11_display_offset; /* What DISPLAY number to start
103 * searching at */
104 int x11_use_localhost; /* If true, use localhost for fake X11 server. */
105 char *xauth_location; /* Location of xauth program */
106 int permit_tty; /* If false, deny pty allocation */
107 int permit_user_rc; /* If false, deny ~/.ssh/rc execution */
108 int strict_modes; /* If true, require string home dir modes. */
109 int tcp_keep_alive; /* If true, set SO_KEEPALIVE. */
110 int ip_qos_interactive; /* IP ToS/DSCP/class for interactive */
111 int ip_qos_bulk; /* IP ToS/DSCP/class for bulk traffic */
112 char *ciphers; /* Supported SSH2 ciphers. */
113 char *macs; /* Supported SSH2 macs. */
114 char *kex_algorithms; /* SSH2 kex methods in order of preference. */
115 struct ForwardOptions fwd_opts; /* forwarding options */
116 SyslogFacility log_facility; /* Facility for system logging. */
117 LogLevel log_level; /* Level for system logging. */
118 int hostbased_authentication; /* If true, permit ssh2 hostbased auth */
119 int hostbased_uses_name_from_packet_only; /* experimental */
120 char *hostbased_key_types; /* Key types allowed for hostbased */
121 char *hostkeyalgorithms; /* SSH2 server key types */
122 char *ca_sign_algorithms; /* Allowed CA signature algorithms */
123 int pubkey_authentication; /* If true, permit ssh2 pubkey authentication. */
124 char *pubkey_key_types; /* Key types allowed for public key */
125 int kerberos_authentication; /* If true, permit Kerberos
126 * authentication. */
127 int kerberos_or_local_passwd; /* If true, permit kerberos
128 * and any other password
129 * authentication mechanism,
130 * such as SecurID or
131 * /etc/passwd */
132 int kerberos_ticket_cleanup; /* If true, destroy ticket
133 * file on logout. */
134 int kerberos_tgt_passing; /* If true, permit Kerberos TGT
135 * passing. */
136 int kerberos_get_afs_token; /* If true, try to get AFS token if
137 * authenticated with Kerberos. */
138#ifdef AFS
139 int afs_token_passing; /* If true, permit AFS token passing. */
140#endif
141 int gss_authentication; /* If true, permit GSSAPI authentication */
142 int gss_cleanup_creds; /* If true, destroy cred cache on logout */
143 int gss_strict_acceptor; /* If true, restrict the GSSAPI acceptor name */
144 int password_authentication; /* If true, permit password
145 * authentication. */
146 int kbd_interactive_authentication; /* If true, permit */
147 int challenge_response_authentication;
148 int permit_empty_passwd; /* If false, do not permit empty
149 * passwords. */
150 int permit_user_env; /* If true, read ~/.ssh/environment */
151 char *permit_user_env_whitelist; /* pattern-list whitelist */
152 int compression; /* If true, compression is allowed */
153 int allow_tcp_forwarding; /* One of FORWARD_* */
154 int allow_streamlocal_forwarding; /* One of FORWARD_* */
155 int allow_agent_forwarding;
156 int disable_forwarding;
157 u_int num_allow_users;
158 char **allow_users;
159 u_int num_deny_users;
160 char **deny_users;
161 u_int num_allow_groups;
162 char **allow_groups;
163 u_int num_deny_groups;
164 char **deny_groups;
165
166 u_int num_subsystems;
167 char *subsystem_name[MAX_SUBSYSTEMS];
168 char *subsystem_command[MAX_SUBSYSTEMS];
169 char *subsystem_args[MAX_SUBSYSTEMS];
170
171 u_int num_accept_env;
172 char **accept_env;
173 u_int num_setenv;
174 char **setenv;
175
176 int max_startups_begin;
177 int max_startups_rate;
178 int max_startups;
179 int max_authtries;
180 int max_sessions;
181 char *banner; /* SSH-2 banner message */
182 int use_dns;
183 int client_alive_interval; /*
184 * poke the client this often to
185 * see if it's still there
186 */
187 int client_alive_count_max; /*
188 * If the client is unresponsive
189 * for this many intervals above,
190 * disconnect the session
191 */
192
193 u_int num_authkeys_files; /* Files containing public keys */
194 char **authorized_keys_files;
195
196 int use_pam; /* Enable auth via PAM */
197 int none_enabled; /* enable NONE cipher switch */
198 int tcp_rcv_buf_poll; /* poll tcp rcv window in autotuning kernels*/
199 int hpn_disabled; /* disable hpn functionality. false by default */
200 int hpn_buffer_size; /* set the hpn buffer size - default 3MB */
201
202 char *adm_forced_command;
203
204 int permit_tun;
205#ifdef WITH_LDAP_PUBKEY
206 ldap_opt_t lpk;
207#endif
208
209 char **permitted_opens; /* May also be one of PERMITOPEN_* */
210 u_int num_permitted_opens;
211 char **permitted_listens; /* May also be one of PERMITOPEN_* */
212 u_int num_permitted_listens;
213
214 char *chroot_directory;
215 char *revoked_keys_file;
216 char *trusted_user_ca_keys;
217 char *authorized_keys_command;
218 char *authorized_keys_command_user;
219 char *authorized_principals_file;
220 char *authorized_principals_command;
221 char *authorized_principals_command_user;
222
223 int64_t rekey_limit;
224 int rekey_interval;
225
226 char *version_addendum; /* Appended to SSH banner */
227
228 u_int num_auth_methods;
229 char **auth_methods;
230
231 int fingerprint_hash;
232 int expose_userauth_info;
233 u_int64_t timing_secret;
234} ServerOptions;
235
236/* Information about the incoming connection as used by Match */
237struct connection_info {
238 const char *user;
239 const char *host; /* possibly resolved hostname */
240 const char *address; /* remote address */
241 const char *laddress; /* local address */
242 int lport; /* local port */
243 const char *rdomain; /* routing domain if available */
244};
245
246
247/*
248 * These are string config options that must be copied between the
249 * Match sub-config and the main config, and must be sent from the
250 * privsep slave to the privsep master. We use a macro to ensure all
251 * the options are copied and the copies are done in the correct order.
252 *
253 * NB. an option must appear in servconf.c:copy_set_server_options() or
254 * COPY_MATCH_STRING_OPTS here but never both.
255 */
256#define COPY_MATCH_STRING_OPTS() do { \
257 M_CP_STROPT(banner); \
258 M_CP_STROPT(trusted_user_ca_keys); \
259 M_CP_STROPT(revoked_keys_file); \
260 M_CP_STROPT(authorized_keys_command); \
261 M_CP_STROPT(authorized_keys_command_user); \
262 M_CP_STROPT(authorized_principals_file); \
263 M_CP_STROPT(authorized_principals_command); \
264 M_CP_STROPT(authorized_principals_command_user); \
265 M_CP_STROPT(hostbased_key_types); \
266 M_CP_STROPT(pubkey_key_types); \
267 M_CP_STROPT(ca_sign_algorithms); \
268 M_CP_STROPT(routing_domain); \
269 M_CP_STROPT(permit_user_env_whitelist); \
270 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(authorized_keys_files, num_authkeys_files); \
271 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(allow_users, num_allow_users); \
272 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(deny_users, num_deny_users); \
273 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(allow_groups, num_allow_groups); \
274 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(deny_groups, num_deny_groups); \
275 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(accept_env, num_accept_env); \
276 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(auth_methods, num_auth_methods); \
277 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(permitted_opens, num_permitted_opens); \
278 M_CP_STRARRAYOPT(permitted_listens, num_permitted_listens); \
279 } while (0)
